text: Yeah, I think it's helpful to think of crypto networks as marketplaces. Uber, Airbnb, traditional web, two marketplaces, the value of those marketplaces is due to the switching cost of moving to an alternative. So anyone could build a competing Airbnb service or a competitor to Uber, but it's hard to get all the users that those platforms have amassed to switch over. And so switching costs is what's at the core of defensibility of Web Two platforms. It's also what's at the core of defensibility of crypto networks.
